<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Svaha — Install (click to copy)</title>
<style>
  :root{ color-scheme: light only; }
  *{ box-sizing:border-box; }
  html,body{ background:#f5f7fa; color:#1a1d24; margin:0; }
  body{ font-family:-apple-system,"Helvetica Neue",Arial,sans-serif; font-size:15px; line-height:1.55; }
  .wrap{ max-width:840px; margin:0 auto; padding:26px 18px 90px; }
  h1{ font-size:28px; margin:0 0 4px; letter-spacing:-0.4px; }
  h2{ font-size:20px; margin:34px 0 10px; padding-bottom:7px; border-bottom:2px solid #1a1d24; }
  h3{ font-size:15px; margin:20px 0 6px; color:#0b3d6b; }
  .sub{ color:#5b5f67; font-size:15px; margin:0 0 4px; }
  .meta{ color:#8a8f98; font-size:12px; }
  p{ margin:8px 0; }
  code{ font-family:"SF Mono",Menlo,Consolas,monospace; font-size:13px; background:#e7ebf1; padding:1px 5px; border-radius:4px; color:#15324f; }
  .where{ display:inline-block; padding:2px 9px; border-radius:5px; font-size:11px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:.4px; color:#fff; text-transform:uppercase; vertical-align:middle; }
  .term{ background:#1f7a46; } .edit{ background:#9a6a00; } .chat{ background:#1c64b3; }
  .cmd{ display:flex; align-items:stretch; margin:8px 0; border-radius:9px; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 1px 3px rgba(20,40,70,.12); }
  .cmd pre{ flex:1; margin:0; padding:12px 14px; background:#15202e; color:#e8edf3;
            font-family:"SF Mono",Menlo,Consolas,monospace; font-size:13px; line-height:1.5; white-space:pre-wrap; word-break:break-word; }
  .cmd button{ flex:0 0 86px; border:0; background:#27384b; color:#cfe0f2; font-weight:700; font-size:13px; cursor:pointer; transition:background .15s; border-left:1px solid #0d1622; }
  .cmd button:hover{ background:#33495f; } .cmd button.ok{ background:#1f7a46; color:#fff; }
  .step{ background:#fff; border:1px solid #e1e6ee; border-radius:11px; padding:14px 16px; margin:12px 0; }
  .step .h{ font-weight:700; margin-bottom:2px; }
  .step .n{ display:inline-block; min-width:24px; height:24px; line-height:24px; text-align:center; background:#1a1d24; color:#fff; border-radius:50%; font-size:13px; font-weight:700; margin-right:8px; }
  .box{ border-radius:10px; padding:12px 15px; margin:14px 0; border:1px solid; }
  .box p:first-child{ margin-top:0; } .box p:last-child{ margin-bottom:0; }
  .lbl{ font-weight:800; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:11px; letter-spacing:.6px; display:block; margin-bottom:3px; }
  .warn{ background:#fff8e8; border-color:#e6c870; } .warn .lbl{ color:#9a6a00; }
  .tip{ background:#eef9f0; border-color:#9bd0a8; } .tip .lbl{ color:#1f7a46; }
  .note{ background:#eef4fb; border-color:#aac6e6; } .note .lbl{ color:#0b5cad; }
  .expect{ font-family:"SF Mono",Menlo,Consolas,monospace; font-size:12px; color:#41506a; background:#eef2f7; border-left:3px solid #9db4cf; padding:7px 11px; margin:2px 0 6px; border-radius:0 5px 5px 0; }
  .expect b{ color:#1f7a46; }
  table{ border-collapse:collapse; width:100%; margin:10px 0; font-size:13px; background:#fff; }
  th,td{ border:1px solid #d8deea; padding:7px 9px; text-align:left; vertical-align:top; } th{ background:#eef1f5; }
  .legend{ background:#fff; border:1px solid #e1e6ee; border-radius:11px; padding:13px 16px; margin:14px 0; font-size:14px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

  <h1>Svaha — Install</h1>
  <p class="sub">From scratch, click-to-copy. Every command has a <b>Copy</b> button — paste it into a Terminal, press return.</p>
  <p class="meta">Open this file in any browser. No internet needed for the page itself.</p>

  <div class="legend">
    <span class="where term">Terminal</span> = a shell window — paste &amp; run. &nbsp;
    <span class="where edit">Edit file</span> = open a file in a text editor. &nbsp;
    <span class="where chat">Claude</span> = type into a running Claude Code session.
  </div>

  <h2>0 · Prerequisites</h2>
  <div class="box note">
    <p><span class="lbl">Never used Claude Code before?</span></p>
    <p>This page installs <b>Svaha on top of Claude Code</b> — it assumes <code>claude</code> already runs. If you're starting from a fresh Mac, do <b><code>INSTALL-CLAUDE-CODE.html</code> first</b> (in this same folder): it installs Claude Code, logs you in, and sets up <code>git</code> + <code>python3</code> so the check below comes up all green. Then come back here.</p>
  </div>
  <p><span class="where term">Terminal</span> Check you have the three things Svaha needs. Each should print a version, not "command not found":</p>
  <div class="cmd"><pre>claude --version && python3 --version && git --version</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
  <div class="expect">If <b>claude</b> is missing → install Claude Code first (see <b>INSTALL-CLAUDE-CODE.html</b>). If <b>python3</b> is missing → install Python 3 (the guard hooks need it). <b>git</b> is only needed for the clone in Step 1 — you can download the folder instead.</div>

  <h2>1 · Get Svaha</h2>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">1</span><span class="where term">Terminal</span> &nbsp;Clone it and move into the folder:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>git clone https://github.com/88k8sh/svaha && cd svaha</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <div class="expect">No git? Download the repo as a ZIP, unzip it, then <code>cd</code> into the unzipped folder instead.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="box warn">
    <p><span class="lbl">Keep this folder where it is</span></p>
    <p>The hooks reference this folder's <code>bin/</code> scripts by absolute path. Put it somewhere permanent (e.g. <code>~/svaha</code>) <b>before</b> Step 3 — if you move it later, the guards stop firing.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>2 · Run the installer</h2>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">2</span><span class="where term">Terminal</span> &nbsp;Copies the 6 slash commands + the hook scripts into <code>~/.claude/</code>. Non-destructive — it asks before touching an existing <code>CLAUDE.md</code>. Answer its prompts:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>./setup.sh</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
  </div>

  <h2>3 · Wire the hooks + permissions <span style="font-size:13px;color:#9a6a00">(the one fiddly step — made easy)</span></h2>
  <p>This merges <code>settings.json.snippet</code> into your Claude config, with this folder's path filled in for <code>&lt;system-dir&gt;</code>. Pick the path that matches you:</p>

  <h3>3A · If you do NOT already have a <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> (most new installs)</h3>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">3A</span><span class="where term">Terminal</span> &nbsp;<b>Run this from inside the svaha folder.</b> It strips the comments, fills in <code>&lt;system-dir&gt;</code> with your real path, writes the file, and checks it's valid — one paste:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>mkdir -p ~/.claude && sed '/^[[:space:]]*\/\//d' settings.json.snippet | sed "s|<system-dir>|$(pwd)|g" > ~/.claude/settings.json && python3 -m json.tool ~/.claude/settings.json >/dev/null && echo "OK — settings.json written and valid"</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <div class="expect">prints <b>OK — settings.json written and valid</b>. If it prints a JSON error instead, nothing was broken — re-run from the correct folder.</div>
  </div>

  <h3>3B · If you ALREADY have a <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code></h3>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">3B</span><span class="where edit">Edit file</span> &nbsp;Open <code>settings.json.snippet</code> and your existing <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>, then:</div>
    <p style="margin:6px 0 0">1. In the snippet, replace every <code>&lt;system-dir&gt;</code> with this folder's full path. Get it with:</p>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>pwd</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <p style="margin:6px 0 0">2. Merge the snippet's <code>"permissions"</code> and <code>"hooks"</code> blocks into your settings.json (if you already have those keys, merge per-array / per-event — don't replace the whole object). 3. Validate:</p>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>python3 -m json.tool ~/.claude/settings.json >/dev/null && echo "valid JSON"</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
  </div>

  <div class="box note">
    <p><span class="lbl">Choose your edit mode (optional)</span></p>
    <p>The snippet ships <b>Mode A</b>: editing is granted once at install, so Claude edits files without re-asking. Reads/inspection are always silent; <code>git push</code>, <code>rm</code>, network, and secret-reads are always gated. <b>Prefer to be asked once per session before edits?</b> Open <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code> and delete the three lines <code>"Edit(**)"</code>, <code>"Write(**)"</code>, <code>"MultiEdit(**)"</code> from the <code>"allow"</code> array. The snippet's header comment explains both.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>4 · Boot it</h2>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">4</span><span class="where term">Terminal</span> &nbsp;Go to any project (or stay here) and start Claude Code:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>claude</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <div class="h" style="margin-top:8px"><span class="where chat">Claude</span> &nbsp;Boot the system:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>/session</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <div class="expect">It boots and prints a <b>proof-of-boot line</b> listing the files it loaded. A brand-new project has nothing to resume yet — that's correct.</div>
  </div>

  <h2>5 · Confirm it worked</h2>
  <div class="step">
    <div class="h"><span class="n">5</span><span class="where term">Terminal</span> &nbsp;The 6 commands and 6 hooks should be in place:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>ls ~/.claude/commands && echo "---" && ls ~/.claude/hooks</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <div class="expect">commands: <b>boot.md session.md handoff.md reflect.md audit.md foldin.md</b>
hooks: the six <b>*.sh</b> files (context-canary, launchpad-nudge, memory-reflect, resume-line-guard, session-end-backstop, session-start-marker)</div>
    <div class="h" style="margin-top:8px"><span class="where chat">Claude</span> &nbsp;And let the system check its own coherence:</div>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>/audit</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
  </div>

  <div class="box tip">
    <p><span class="lbl">Just want the behavior, not the full loop?</span></p>
    <p>Skip the scaffold — drop the contract in and you're done (no handoff loop, no hooks):</p>
    <div class="cmd"><pre>cp CLAUDE.md ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md</pre><button onclick="cp(this)">Copy</button></div>
    <p>Global for every project, or use <code>cp CLAUDE.md ./CLAUDE.md</code> to scope it to one repo.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>6 · If something snags</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Fix</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Hooks never fire / commands behave oddly</td><td>Your <code>settings.json</code> is probably invalid JSON or still has a literal <code>&lt;system-dir&gt;</code>. Re-run the validate: <code>python3 -m json.tool ~/.claude/settings.json</code> — fix what it flags.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>python3: command not found</code></td><td>Install Python 3 — the guard hooks (`security-guard.py`, etc.) are Python.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>A guard complains it can't find a <code>bin/</code> script</td><td>The svaha folder moved. Either move it back, or re-do Step 3 so <code>&lt;system-dir&gt;</code> points at its new path.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>/session</code> says "nothing to resume"</td><td>Expected on a fresh project — there's no prior handoff yet. Do some work, then <code>/handoff</code>, and the next <code>/session</code> will recover it.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>command pasted weirdly / "command not found"</td><td>Use the <b>Copy</b> button (it copies the exact text) — don't hand-select, which can grab stray characters.</td></tr>
  </table>

  <p class="meta" style="margin-top:22px">Full reference: <code>README.md</code> · the behavior contract: <code>CLAUDE.md</code> · the why: <code>docs/essay.md</code></p>
</div>

<script>
  function cp(btn){
    var text = btn.parentNode.querySelector('pre').textContent;
    function flash(){ var o = btn.textContent; btn.textContent='Copied!'; btn.classList.add('ok');
      setTimeout(function(){ btn.textContent=o; btn.classList.remove('ok'); }, 1200); }
    function fallback(){ var ta=document.createElement('textarea'); ta.value=text; ta.style.position='fixed';
      ta.style.top='0'; ta.style.opacity='0'; document.body.appendChild(ta); ta.focus(); ta.select();
      try{ document.execCommand('copy'); }catch(e){} document.body.removeChild(ta); }
    if(navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText){
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(flash, function(){ fallback(); flash(); });
    } else { fallback(); flash(); }
  }
</script>
</body>
</html>
